{"title_page": "Requiem and Silence", "text_new": "{{Infobox album\n| name       = Requiem and Silence\n| type       = compilation\n| artist     = [[Chihiro Onitsuka]]\n| cover      = Requiem and Silence.jpeg\n| border     = yes\n| alt        = \n| caption    =\n| released   = {{Start date|2020|02|20}}\n| recorded   = 1999\u20132020\n| studio     = \n| genre      = {{hlist|[[J-pop]]|[[rock music|rock]]}}\n| length     = \n| label      = [[JVCKenwood Victor Entertainment|Victor]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = Tiny Screams\n| prev_year  = 2019\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Requiem and Silence\n | type        = compilation\n | single1     = Inori ga Kotoba ni Kawaru Koro\n | single1date = {{start date|2014|05|28}}\n | single2     = Hinagiku\n | single2date = {{start date|2018|08|22}}\n | single3     = End of the World\n | single3date = {{start date|2019|03|27}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Requiem and Silence''''' (stylized in [[all caps]]) is the fifth [[greatest hits album]] by Japanese singer-songwriter [[Chihiro Onitsuka]]. It was released on February 20, 2020 through [[JVCKenwood Victor Entertainment|Victor Entertainment]]. The album was released in three different editions, standard and limited, and premium collector's edition. The album includes a new track: \"Kakikake no Tegami\".\n\n==Commercial performance==\n''Requiem and Silence'' debuted at number two on the [[Oricon]] Daily Albums Chart, and number twelve on the [[Oricon]] Weekly Albums Chart, selling 5,159 copies.\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n|headline = ''Requiem and Silence'' track listing\n| extra_column = Arranger(s)\n| all_writing     = Chihiro Onitsuka, except where noted\n| headline = Standard edition\n\n| title1 = [[Gekk\u014d (song)|Gekk\u014d]]\n| extra1 = [[Takefumi Haketa]]\n\n| title2 = Memai\n| extra2 = Haketa\n\n| title3 = Infection\n| extra3 = Haketa\n\n| title4 = Ry\u016bseigun\n| extra4 = Haketa\n\n| title5 = Ii Hi Tabidachi, Nishi e\n| not