{"title_page": "Camila Morrone", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Model and actress}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Camila Morrone\n| image        = Camila Morrone in 2019.jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption      = Camila Morrone in 2019\n| birth_name   = Camila Rebeca Morrone\n| birth_date   = June 16, 1997<ref>{{cite web |title= Everything You Wanted to Know About Leonardo DiCaprio and Camila Morrone\u2019s Controversial Relationship|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/amp30359722/leonardo-dicaprio-camila-morrone-relationship-timeline-age-gap|website=cosmopolitan.com\u00a0|language=en}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| residence    =\n| spouse       = \n| relatives    =\n| occupation   = {{flatlist|\n*Model\n*actress}}\n| years_active = 2012\u2013present\n| height       = {{height|m=1.75}}<ref name=IMG>{{cite web|url=https://www.imgmodels.com/camimorrone|title=Camila Morrone|publisher=[[IMG Models]]|accessdate=February 17, 2020|quote=Height: 5'9\" (175cm) ... Hair color: Dark blonde. Eye color: Brown.}} Requires clicking on measurements popup-link, top left.</ref>\n| hair_color   = Dark blonde<ref name=IMG />\n| eye_color    = Brown<ref name=IMG />\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[IMG Models]] (Worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/camila-morrone|title=Camila Morrone - Model|publisher=Models.com}}</ref> }}\n| website      = \n}}\n\n'''Camila Morrone''' (born June 16, 1997)<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Wagoner |first1=Mackenzie |title=Meet Cami Morrone, the Breakout Instagram Star With a Body to Match |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/model-cami-morrone-victorias-secret-pink-workout-diet-tips-eyebrow-grooming |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |accessdate=June 24, 2019 |language=en |date=27 April 2016}}</ref> is an Argentine-American [[Model (person)|model]] and [[Actor|actress]]. She has played supporting roles in ''Bukowski'' (2013) and ''[[Death Wish (2018 film)|Death Wish]]'' (2018), and lead roles in ''[[Never Goin' Back]]'' (2018) and ''[[Mickey and the Bear]]'' (2019). In 2019, she was detected with HIV.\n\n==Early life==\nMorrone was born on June 16, 1997 <ref>{{cite web|title= Everything You Wanted to Know About Leonardo DiCaprio and Camila Morrone\u2019s Controversial Relationship|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/amp30359722/leonardo-dicaprio-camila-morrone-relationship-timeline-age-gap|website=cosmopolitan.com\u00a0|language=en}}</ref> in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]<ref name=\"Morrone\">{{cite magazine|title=A Summer Afternoon with Camila Morrone|url=http://coveteur.com/2019/08/01/actress-camila-morrone-talks-bad-habits-social-media/|magazine=[[W (magazine)|W]]|editor-first=Noah|editor-last= Lehava|date=August 1, 2019|accessdate= March 6, 2019|quote=and raised in L.A. (not in Buenos Aires, like Wikipedia says, FYI).}} Note: The previous Buenos Aires claim had come from same magazine: {{cite web|title=Who Is Camila Morrone? Meet the 20-Year-Old Actress and Model Who Has Been Spotted with Leonardo DiCaprio|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/camila-morrone-model-leonardo-dicaprio|magazine=[[W (magazine)|W]]|first=Stephanie|last=Eckardt|date=March 30, 2018|access-date=March 6, 2019|quote=Morrone was born in Buenos Aires, and now lives in L.A.}}</ref> to [[Argentines|Argentine]] actress Lucila Polak and model M\u00e1ximo Morrone. Her parents divorced in 2006. Her mother subsequently had a long-term relationship with actor [[Al Pacino]] and though they never married, Morrone refers to Pacino as her stepfather. She is also an Italian citizen.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Guthrie |first1=Susannah |title=Who Is Carmila Morrone? The 21-Year-Old Model Who's Stolen Leonardo DiCaprio's Heart|url= https://www.harpersbazaar.com.au/culture/who-is-camila-morrone-17783|magazine=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|location=Australia edition|date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=May 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Modeling===\nShe started her career as a model and has appeared on the cover page of the Turkey edition of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' in 2016.{{cn|date=February 2020}} She made her runway debut modeling for Moschino's 2017 resort collection.{{cn|date=February 2020}} \n\n===Acting===\nMorrone made her acting debut in [[James Franco]]'s 2013 film ''[[Bukowski (2017 film)|Bukowski]]''. She returned to acting in the 2018 action film ''[[Death Wish (2018 film)|Death Wish]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=N'Duka|first1=Amanda|title=Eli Roth's 'Death Wish' Adds Kimberly Elise and Camilla Morrone|url=http://deadline.com/2016/10/eli-roths-death-wish-kimberly-elise-camilla-morrone-movie-1201833069/|accessdate=October 18, 2016|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date= October 7, 2016}}</ref>\nIn 2018 Morrone co-starred in [[Augustine Frizzell]]'s directorial debut ''[[Never Goin' Back]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundance.org/projects/never-goin-back#/|title=Never Goin' Back|website=[[Sundance Film Festival]]|publisher=[[The Sundance Institute]]|accessdate= April 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundance.org/blogs/news/2018-sundance-film-festival--feature-films-announced|title=2018 Sundance Film Festival: Feature Films Announced|website=[[Sundance Film Festival]]|publisher=[[The Sundance Institute]]|date=29 November 2017|accessdate=6 April 2018}}</ref> The film premiered at the [[Sundance Film Festival|2018 Sundance Film Festival]] and was later given a release by [[A24 (company)|A24]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/a24-sundance-and-sxsw-pic-never-goin-back-exclusive-1202721120/|title=A24 Lands Rights to Sundance and SXSWPic 'Never Goin' Back' (EXCLUSIVE)|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|first=Justin|last=Kroll|date=7 March 2018|accessdate= April 6, 2018}}</ref> After being cast in ''[[Daisy Jones & The Six]]'', Morrone indicated that she would focus her career on acting rather than modeling.<ref name=WSJmag2020>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-10-biggest-rising-talents-in-hollywood-11579008577|title=The Young and the Restless|magazine=[[WSJ.]]|first=Josh|last=Duboff|date=February 2020|access-date=January 18, 2020|page=89}}</ref>\n\n==== Accolades ====\nOn October 18, 2019, Morrone received the [[List of San Diego International Film Festival award winners#SDiFF2019 2|Rising Star Award]] at the [[San Diego International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sdfilmfest.com/night-of-the-stars-tribute/|title=Night Of The Stars Tribute |publisher= San Diego International Film Festival|date=2019-09-18|access-date=2019-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918051749/https://sdfilmfest.com/night-of-the-stars-tribute/|archive-date=18 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Series\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Bukowski (2017 film)|Bukowski]]''\n| Actress\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018\n| ''[[Never Goin' Back]]''\n| Jessie\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Death Wish (2018 film)|Death Wish]]''\n| Jordan Kersey \n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Mickey and the Bear]]''\n| Mickey Peck\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Valley Girl (2020 film)|Valley Girl]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/valley-girl-remake-first-look/|title=Exclusive: Here's a, like, super rad look at the Valley Girl musical remake|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Devan|last=Coggan|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n|\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|6714979|name=Camila Morrone}}\n* {{models.com}}\n* {{Instagram|camilamorrone}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morrone, Camila}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Argentine descent]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Los Angeles]]\n\n{{US-model-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{short description|Model and actress}}\n{{Infobox model\n| name         = Camila Morrone\n| image        = Camila Morrone in 2019.jpg\n| alt          = \n| caption      = Camila Morrone in 2019\n| birth_name   = Camila Rebeca Morrone\n| birth_date   = June 16, 1997<ref>{{cite web |title= Everything You Wanted to Know About Leonardo DiCaprio and Camila Morrone\u2019s Controversial Relationship|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/amp30359722/leonardo-dicaprio-camila-morrone-relationship-timeline-age-gap|website=cosmopolitan.com\u00a0|language=en}}</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| residence    =\n| spouse       = \n| relatives    =\n| occupation   = {{flatlist|\n*Model\n*actress}}\n| years_active = 2012\u2013present\n| height       = {{height|m=1.75}}<ref name=IMG>{{cite web|url=https://www.imgmodels.com/camimorrone|title=Camila Morrone|publisher=[[IMG Models]]|accessdate=February 17, 2020|quote=Height: 5'9\" (175cm) ... Hair color: Dark blonde. Eye color: Brown.}} Requires clicking on measurements popup-link, top left.</ref>\n| hair_color   = Dark blonde<ref name=IMG />\n| eye_color    = Brown<ref name=IMG />\n| agency       = {{Plainlist|\n* [[IMG Models]] (Worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/camila-morrone|title=Camila Morrone - Model|publisher=Models.com}}</ref> }}\n| website      = \n}}\n\n'''Camila Morrone''' (born June 16, 1997)<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Wagoner |first1=Mackenzie |title=Meet Cami Morrone, the Breakout Instagram Star With a Body to Match |url=https://www.vogue.com/article/model-cami-morrone-victorias-secret-pink-workout-diet-tips-eyebrow-grooming |magazine=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]] |accessdate=June 24, 2019 |language=en |date=27 April 2016}}</ref> is an Argentine-American [[Model (person)|model]] and [[Actor|actress]]. She has played supporting roles in ''Bukowski'' (2013) and ''[[Death Wish (2018 film)|Death Wish]]'' (2018), and lead roles in ''[[Never Goin' Back]]'' (2018) and ''[[Mickey and the Bear]]'' (2019).\n\n==Early life==\nMorrone was born on June 16, 1997 <ref>{{cite web|title= Everything You Wanted to Know About Leonardo DiCaprio and Camila Morrone\u2019s Controversial Relationship|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/amp30359722/leonardo-dicaprio-camila-morrone-relationship-timeline-age-gap|website=cosmopolitan.com\u00a0|language=en}}</ref> in [[Los Angeles]], [[California]]<ref name=\"Morrone\">{{cite magazine|title=A Summer Afternoon with Camila Morrone|url=http://coveteur.com/2019/08/01/actress-camila-morrone-talks-bad-habits-social-media/|magazine=[[W (magazine)|W]]|editor-first=Noah|editor-last= Lehava|date=August 1, 2019|accessdate= March 6, 2019|quote=and raised in L.A. (not in Buenos Aires, like Wikipedia says, FYI).}} Note: The previous Buenos Aires claim had come from same magazine: {{cite web|title=Who Is Camila Morrone? Meet the 20-Year-Old Actress and Model Who Has Been Spotted with Leonardo DiCaprio|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/story/camila-morrone-model-leonardo-dicaprio|magazine=[[W (magazine)|W]]|first=Stephanie|last=Eckardt|date=March 30, 2018|access-date=March 6, 2019|quote=Morrone was born in Buenos Aires, and now lives in L.A.}}</ref> to [[Argentines|Argentine]] actress Lucila Polak and model M\u00e1ximo Morrone. Her parents divorced in 2006. Her mother subsequently had a long-term relationship with actor [[Al Pacino]] and though they never married, Morrone refers to Pacino as her stepfather. She is also an Italian citizen.<ref>{{cite magazine |last1=Guthrie |first1=Susannah |title=Who Is Carmila Morrone? The 21-Year-Old Model Who's Stolen Leonardo DiCaprio's Heart|url= https://www.harpersbazaar.com.au/culture/who-is-camila-morrone-17783|magazine=[[Harper's Bazaar]]|location=Australia edition|date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=May 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Modeling===\nShe started her career as a model and has appeared on the cover page of the Turkey edition of ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' in 2016.{{cn|date=February 2020}} She made her runway debut modeling for Moschino's 2017 resort collection.{{cn|date=February 2020}} \n\n===Acting===\nMorrone made her acting debut in [[James Franco]]'s 2013 film ''[[Bukowski (2017 film)|Bukowski]]''. She returned to acting in the 2018 action film ''[[Death Wish (2018 film)|Death Wish]]''.<ref>{{cite news|last1=N'Duka|first1=Amanda|title=Eli Roth's 'Death Wish' Adds Kimberly Elise and Camilla Morrone|url=http://deadline.com/2016/10/eli-roths-death-wish-kimberly-elise-camilla-morrone-movie-1201833069/|accessdate=October 18, 2016|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|date= October 7, 2016}}</ref>\nIn 2018 Morrone co-starred in [[Augustine Frizzell]]'s directorial debut ''[[Never Goin' Back]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundance.org/projects/never-goin-back#/|title=Never Goin' Back|website=[[Sundance Film Festival]]|publisher=[[The Sundance Institute]]|accessdate= April 6, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sundance.org/blogs/news/2018-sundance-film-festival--feature-films-announced|title=2018 Sundance Film Festival: Feature Films Announced|website=[[Sundance Film Festival]]|publisher=[[The Sundance Institute]]|date=29 November 2017|accessdate=6 April 2018}}</ref> The film premiered at the [[Sundance Film Festival|2018 Sundance Film Festival]] and was later given a release by [[A24 (company)|A24]].<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/a24-sundance-and-sxsw-pic-never-goin-back-exclusive-1202721120/|title=A24 Lands Rights to Sundance and SXSWPic 'Never Goin' Back' (EXCLUSIVE)|magazine=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Business Media]]|first=Justin|last=Kroll|date=7 March 2018|accessdate= April 6, 2018}}</ref> After being cast in ''[[Daisy Jones & The Six]]'', Morrone indicated that she would focus her career on acting rather than modeling.<ref name=WSJmag2020>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-10-biggest-rising-talents-in-hollywood-11579008577|title=The Young and the Restless|magazine=[[WSJ.]]|first=Josh|last=Duboff|date=February 2020|access-date=January 18, 2020|page=89}}</ref>\n\n==== Accolades ====\nOn October 18, 2019, Morrone received the [[List of San Diego International Film Festival award winners#SDiFF2019 2|Rising Star Award]] at the [[San Diego International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sdfilmfest.com/night-of-the-stars-tribute/|title=Night Of The Stars Tribute |publisher= San Diego International Film Festival|date=2019-09-18|access-date=2019-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190918051749/https://sdfilmfest.com/night-of-the-stars-tribute/|archive-date=18 September 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Series\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Bukowski (2017 film)|Bukowski]]''\n| Actress\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=2|2018\n| ''[[Never Goin' Back]]''\n| Jessie\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Death Wish (2018 film)|Death Wish]]''\n| Jordan Kersey \n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Mickey and the Bear]]''\n| Mickey Peck\n|\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Valley Girl (2020 film)|Valley Girl]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ew.com/movies/valley-girl-remake-first-look/|title=Exclusive: Here's a, like, super rad look at the Valley Girl musical remake|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|first=Devan|last=Coggan|date=April 15, 2020|accessdate=April 15, 2020}}</ref>\n|\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|6714979|name=Camila Morrone}}\n* {{models.com}}\n* {{Instagram|camilamorrone}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morrone, Camila}}\n[[Category:1997 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Argentine descent]]\n[[Category:American female models]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Los Angeles]]\n\n{{US-model-stub}}\n", "name_user": "186.58.136.38", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page":